1 create package.json - npm init
2 create node modules - install express - npm i express
3 create index.js file
4 import express inside the index.js
5 using express create an app
6 setup port number
7 use json parser for srever application
8 install cors for connect frontend and backend  - npm i cors
9 import cors
10 using cors specify origin to the server(integration)
11 api fetch - fakestoreapi/products
12 create db and collection in mongodb
13 for access data inside mongodb we use mongoose (establish the connections btwn the server) - npm i mongoose
14 create a folder - servises and create 2 files
    db.js and dataService.js

15 in db.js - import mongoose to establish the connections 
16 define connection string
17 create model and schema
18 export model
19  import db  in dataService , create a function and export it
20 resolving api request in index.js.....before it...implement login in data service
finally index and dataservices connected...node +mongodb connection successfull..
